---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Segment Marketing Plan" section="segment-plan">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Strategy · Go-to-Market by Segment</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Three audiences, <em>three plans.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Jim's framing: two B2B prongs — SMB practices + Enterprise/DSO — <em>plus</em> the new direct-to-patient leg previous teams never built. Each segment gets its own objective, message, channels, and first builds, so you can start shipping.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>The new third leg — <strong>direct-to-patient membership marketing</strong> — is both the priority mandate and the growth multiplier: more members per practice = stickier practices (retention + expansion) <em>and</em> a demand engine that helps win new practices. SMB and Enterprise are the B2B prongs you already have intel for. Patient is the build-from-scratch leg, and it's gated by anti-kickback compliance: <strong>inform, never incentivize.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="segment-plan"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">First builds shipped: <span data-progress-here="segment-plan">0 / 0</span></p>

  <h2>The flywheel that connects them</h2>
  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <p style="margin:0">Win a practice (SMB/Enterprise) → help it enroll more members (Patient) → more members make the practice stickier and more valuable (retention + Bridge Pro expansion) → happy high-member practices become references + case studies → that proof wins the next practice. Patient marketing isn't a side channel — it's the loop that makes the B2B motion compound. Per Judd: the members ultimately pay for the service, yet today nothing markets to them directly. That's the gap.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SMB -->
  <h2>Segment 1 · SMB practices <span class="pill pill-zest">B2B prong</span></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Who:</strong> independent + small group practices (1-9 locations). Buyers: office manager / front-desk lead and the dentist-owner. Fast ~13-day sales cycle, 1-2 stakeholders.</p>
    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> volume demand-gen → demo requests → self-serve-ish close. This is your highest-velocity acquisition motion.</p>
    <p><strong>Message:</strong> "Fire your insurance company" — reclaim margin + patient relationships without going cash-only. The real competitor is <a href="/clerri/competitors">DIY in-house plans</a>, so lead with the licensing/liability + discount-leakage wedge, not feature lists.</p>
    <p><strong>Channels:</strong> paid search (Google), paid social (Meta — currently paused for budget; the unpause decision is yours), comparison/alternatives SEO content (own it post-Loudspeaker), AADOM + small trade-show booths, email nurture. Conversion via the demo form → Chili Piper.</p>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First builds:</strong> (1) revive + instrument the demo-request funnel; (2) the "DIY vs. Clerri" content piece (the actual loss column); (3) a real email nurture sequence (replaces 7knots' generic templates); (4) decide the Meta unpause with Opascope.</p>
    <div data-section="segment-plan"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="sp-smb-01" data-section="segment-plan" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">SMB: revive demo funnel + ship "DIY vs Clerri" + nurture sequence</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ENTERPRISE -->
  <h2>Segment 2 · Enterprise / DSO <span class="pill pill-zest">B2B prong</span></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Who:</strong> DSOs + multi-location groups. Buying committee: C-suite (CEO/CFO/COO), RCM leaders, ops VPs/directors, CMOs, payer-relations. Account-based, longer consultative cycle. Live example: the 287-location DCA deal.</p>
    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> account-based pipeline — get Clerri <em>invited into more deals earlier</em> (per the battlecard, you win ~100% once you're in; the gap is awareness). Quality over volume.</p>
    <p><strong>Message:</strong> scale + proof (7 of top 10 DSOs), compliance/DMPO licensing as risk-transfer, proven implementation, Bridge Pro automation + ledger write-back. Counter Subscribili's "old school" FUD with the <a href="/clerri/competitors">battlecard</a>.</p>
    <p><strong>Channels:</strong> ABM (1:1 / 1:few against the ~170-account target list + Bombora intent), conferences (ADSO, Becker's, GDN — small high-impact booths per Jim), content syndication (the CPL buys), LinkedIn, founder/exec-led content.</p>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First builds:</strong> (1) case studies (Midtown 46% / 7-to-7 $4.5M / SkyRidge 8X — verify sourcing first); (2) battlecard-driven sales enablement; (3) the <strong>Bridge Pro expansion campaign</strong> to the 90-95% not using it (existing-base growth, Jim's priority); (4) the ABM target-account play.</p>
    <div data-section="segment-plan"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="sp-ent-01" data-section="segment-plan" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Enterprise: case studies + battlecard enablement + Bridge Pro expansion + ABM plays</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <!-- PATIENT -->
  <h2>Segment 3 · Patients / Members <span class="pill pill-wine">NEW — the mandate</span></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <div class="callout wine" style="margin-top:0">
      <div class="lbl">⚠️ Read this before building anything for this segment</div>
      <p style="margin:0">For member outreach, Clerri must act like an <strong>insurance company</strong> regulatorily. Anti-kickback laws mean you <strong>INFORM</strong> patients about membership options — never <strong>INCENTIVIZE</strong> (no "sign up and get $X"). <strong>Define the guardrails with legal before any campaign ships.</strong> This is the gate on the whole segment.</p>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>Who:</strong> patients of Clerri practices — today the focus is cash-pay patients; the mandate is to expand to <em>all</em> patients (uninsured + insured). Note: these are the practices' patients, so comms are practice-branded / on behalf of the practice.</p>
    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> drive membership <em>enrollment</em> inside existing practices — the revenue lever Judd flagged (members ultimately pay, yet nothing markets to them today). Front-desk staff can't carry this (turnover, no sales focus), so marketing automates it.</p>
    <p><strong>Message:</strong> purely informational — "Your dentist offers a membership plan. Here's what it covers and what it saves you." Educational, not promotional-with-incentives. Plain, clear, compliant.</p>
    <p><strong>Channels:</strong> automated email campaigns (the thing prior teams never built), the patient <a href="/clerri/directory">directory</a> ("find a Clerri practice"), practice-branded patient touchpoints, portal/onboarding moments.</p>
    <p class="grab"><strong>First builds (in order):</strong> (1) <strong>compliance guardrails with legal</strong> — the gate; (2) coordinate with Nik + Jacob on a clean, separate member list (don't message members as prospects — the botched-campaign risk); (3) an informational patient-education email template; (4) an enrollment-nudge sequence (informational only); (5) tie it to the directory.</p>
    <div data-section="segment-plan"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="sp-pat-01" data-section="segment-plan" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Patient: legal guardrails FIRST → clean member list → education template → informational nudge sequence</div></div></label></div>
  </div>

  <h2>Cross-cutting — <em>true for all three.</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card"><h4>List hygiene</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Coordinate with Nik + Jacob so customers, members, and prospects are cleanly separated. Never send prospect content to customers/members (the John Lowe incident). Members stay a distinct list.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Compliance</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Patient = anti-kickback / insurance-like rules. B2B = standard. Build the patient guardrails once, with legal, and reuse.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Measurement</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Tie each segment to the funnel in HubSpot (Original Source → lifecycle → revenue once the SF deal-sync lands). Patient enrollment is a new metric to stand up.</p></div>
  </div>

  <h2>Build first — <em>the 90-day sequence.</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-mint">Weeks 1-4</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Unblock + foundations</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Patient compliance guardrails (legal); clean lists with Nik; Meta-unpause decision; revive SMB demo funnel. In-source the email engine off 7knots.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-zest">Weeks 5-8</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Ship the first plays</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">SMB nurture + "DIY vs Clerri"; patient education email; Bridge Pro expansion campaign; case studies (verified). The 5 email ideas → John.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><span class="pill pill-wine">Weeks 9-12</span><h4 style="margin:0.4rem 0">Scale what works</h4><p style="font-size:0.875rem">Patient enrollment-nudge sequence; ABM target-account plays; AEO/historical-PR push; measure + report per segment in the weekly call.</p></div>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Segment plan notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="segment-plan-notes" placeholder="What you ship per segment, what converts, compliance sign-offs, coordination notes with Nik/Jacob/John..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/icp"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">ICP & ABM Targets</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/market"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Market Context</span></a>
  </div>

</div>

<style>
  .card p { font-size:0.92rem; line-height:1.55; margin:0 0 0.6rem; }
  .card .grab { background:rgba(207,252,120,0.18); border-left:3px solid var(--clerri-green); padding:0.5rem 0.75rem; border-radius:0 0.4rem 0.4rem 0; }
  h2 .pill { vertical-align:middle; margin-left:0.4rem; font-size:0.62rem; }
</style>

</ClerriLayout>
